additional_info:
06-03-2011 - Modification Notes
This code manipulates the star button container usually located in the right side of the URL bar. In order for this style to display properly, the URL bar must be fixed in size, allowing no flex sizing to occur.

URL bar size - Modifications to the size of the URL bar should be adjusted by changing values in the following four lines of code equally:
#urlbar-container {
	 min-width: 300px !important;
	 max-width: 300px !important;
}
#star-button[starred="true"] {
	 width: 240px !important;
	 margin-left: -240px !important;
	 
Add or subtract the same amount to each value for all four code lines to increase/decrease the size of the URL bar.

 
Red and CornflowerBlue should be easily modified for color change. Replace CornflowerBlue with transparent for text clarity.

 
Delete the following line if displaying the white, non-bookmarked star is desired:
#star-button:not([starred="true"]),

06-25-2011 - Tested functional with FF5.

css:
@namespace url(http://www.mozilla.org/keymaster/gatekeeper/there.is.only.xul);

#urlbar-container {
	 min-width: 300px !important;
	 max-width: 300px !important;
}
#star-button[starred="true"] {
	 width: 240px !important;
	 margin-left: -240px !important;
	 margin-right: 4px !important;
	 margin-top: -1px !important;
	 outline: solid red 5px !important;
	 opacity: .65 !important;
	 border: CornflowerBlue inset 7px !important;
	 height: 14px !important;
}
#star-button:not([starred="true"]),
#star-button:focus, #star-button:hover, #star-button:active {
	 display: none !important;
}
